description: Numbers n such that n/[largest power of squarefree kernel] is larger than 1.
comments: Complement of A072774 (powers of squarefree numbers).Also numbers n=p(1)^alpha(1)* ... * p(r)^alpha(r) such that RootMeanSquare(alpha(1),...,alpha(r)) is not an integer. - _Ctibor O. Zizka_, Sep 19 2008
links: Donald Alan Morrison, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
example: n=440 is here because n=2.2.2.5.11, its sqf-kernel=110, quotient=4>1.
author: _Labos Elemer_, Jul 18 2001
